&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Account Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the end-to-end success and growth of a portfolio of Elation&#39;s largest, most strategic accounts, including gross revenue retention, net revenue retention, and expansion ARR&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute account plans that reflect each customer&#39;s business goals, organizational dynamics, and clinical priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify and manage retention risks, escalating cross-functionally and setting clear expectations externally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Executive Relationship Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain trusted relationships with C-suite and senior decision-makers across your accounts, including CMOs, CEOs, COOs, and clinical leaders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a strategic advisor and thought partner, helping customers think through how Elation supports their long-term care delivery and business goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead executive business reviews that drive alignment, demonstrate value, and open doors to expansion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commercial Growth&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, develop, and close upsell and cross-sell opportunities in partnership with Sales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate customer challenges and workflows into compelling business cases for expanded Elation adoption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring a commercial mindset to every customer interaction, always thinking about how to deepen the partnership and grow the relationship&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-functional Influence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the voice of your customers internally, advocating for their needs with Product, Engineering, and Operations, and ensuring feedback shapes Elation&#39;s roadmap&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales, Marketing, and Service teams to ensure seamless, cohesive experiences across the customer lifecycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development of frameworks and playbooks that raise the bar for how Elation engages with enterprise customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Insight &amp;amp; Accountability&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own your book of business metrics: health scores, usage trends, risk signals, and expansion pipeline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regularly communicate account status, risks, and opportunities to senior leadership with clarity and commercial context&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain rigorous account documentation to ensure continuity and institutional knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years in Customer Success, Strategic Account Management, or Consulting, with at least 3 years managing enterprise or key accounts at a SaaS company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years

&lt;p&gt;At Elation, our team is committed to enhancing physician and patient quality of life. We are a SaaS cloud-based clinical platform on a mission to enable every patient to receive the highest quality of care. Since inception, we’ve been focused on building a delightful, world‑class customer experience that empowers physicians to focus on delivering phenomenal care to patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re building a clinical-first platform that gives physicians their time back and helps them deliver better care. As healthcare gets more complex, we&#39;re using AI to make it simpler, from clinical documentation to billing to patient engagement. We need a product marketer who gets healthcare and can help us tell that story.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll own go-to-market strategy for our AI and platform products. That means figuring out positioning, running launches, enabling sales, and making sure the market understands what makes us different.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role reports to the Director of Product Marketing and sits at the center of Product, Sales, Marketing, and Enablement teams. You&#39;ll need to understand both the strategic &quot;why&quot; and roll up your sleeves on execution. One day you&#39;re building a competitive battlecard, the next you&#39;re shaping roadmap priorities based on market feedback.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Healthcare is complicated. EHRs are complicated. Medical billing is &lt;em&gt;really&lt;/em&gt; complicated. We need someone who can translate that complexity into clear value propositions that resonate with physicians, practice administrators, and health system buyers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own positioning and strategy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define how we talk about our products (especially our AI capabilities) in ways that land with healthcare buyers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run competitive intelligence and market research to inform product strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build buyer personas and market frameworks that actually get used&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the internal expert on where healthcare SaaS is headed and how we fit in&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Run launches&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead cross-functional teams through product launches, from strategy to execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build launch plans that coordinate across sales, marketing, customer success, and partnerships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create the narratives, proof points, and customer stories that make launches successful&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actually track what works and what doesn&#39;t&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enable revenue teams&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make sales collateral that sellers will actually use: pitch decks, battlecards, demo scripts, objection handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Train Sales and Customer Success on new products and competitive positioning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with our Enablement team to build scalable ways to keep everyone current (we move fast)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Create content that matters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Demand Gen and Content to develop campaigns, webinars, case studies, and thought leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write (or heavily edit) everything from one-pagers to blog posts to keynote content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help establish Elation&#39;s voice in the market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build the function&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As we grow, help define what world-class product marketing looks like at Elation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document what works, create repeatable processes, level up the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must have:&lt;/str

&lt;p&gt;Our team is committed to enhancing physician and patient quality of life through Elation, a SaaS cloud-based clinical platform. Since inception, we&#39;ve been focused on building a delightful, world-class experience that empowers physicians to deliver phenomenal care to patients.&lt;/p&gt;
